defs.name: Reallocator

defs.docs:
A matrix reallocator. Changes the size of the memory buffer that initially contains (RFrom ×
 CFrom) elements to a smaller or larger size (RTo, CTo).

defs.name: reallocate_copy
defs.value: fn (nrows: RTo, ncols: CTo, buf: <Self as Allocator<N, RFrom, CFrom>>::Buffer) -> <Self as Allocator<N, RTo, CTo>>::Buffer

Reallocates a buffer of shape `(RTo, CTo)`, possibly reusing a previously allocated buffer
 `buf`. Data stored by `buf` are linearly copied to the output:

defs.name: try_to_usize
defs.docs:
Gets the compile-time value of `Self`. Returns `None` if it is not known, i.e., if `Self =
 Dynamic`.

defs.name: value
defs.docs:
Gets the run-time value of `self`. For type-level integers, this is the same as
 `Self::try_to_usize().unwrap()`.

defs.name: from_usize
defs.docs:
Builds an instance of `Self` from a run-time value. Panics if `Self` is a type-level
 integer and `dim != Self::try_to_usize().unwrap()`.
